WEBVTT

00:01.460 --> 00:03.246
NARRA TOR:
Previously on Heroes.

00:03.838 --> 00:04.953
I had a dream.

00:05.047 --> 00:06.378
I know what
we have to do now.

00:06.465 --> 00:08.001
We need to bring
this family together.

00:08.092 --> 00:09.878
And then we need
to go visit my sister.

00:09.969 --> 00:13.678
Do you know about
what happened at the place
called Coyote Sands?

00:13.764 --> 00:17.348
When your grandmother has
a dream, it's a good idea
to pay attention.

00:17.810 --> 00:19.095
My father started
writing the government

00:19.187 --> 00:23.226
looking for information
on an abandoned government
project in the 1960s.

00:23.316 --> 00:24.726
If you know something...

00:24.817 --> 00:27.854
Never said what but
it was around the time
his nightmares kicked in.

00:27.945 --> 00:30.231
I could hear him
yelling up here
night after night.

00:30.323 --> 00:33.736
MOHINDER: The files are
heavily redacted, but it
mentions medical research

00:33.826 --> 00:35.908
at a place
called Coyote Sands.

00:35.995 --> 00:37.280
My father was there.

00:38.247 --> 00:39.327
There it is.

00:39.415 --> 00:40.825
Peter and l are
headed there now.

00:40.917 --> 00:43.124
I spoke with Nathan.
He and Claire will meet us.

00:43.211 --> 00:44.246
I need you with us.

00:44.337 --> 00:46.669
This is where
our story really begins.

00:46.756 --> 00:49.793
And to prepare
for the future, you have
to understand the past.

00:49.884 --> 00:50.964
You want the answers?

00:51.052 --> 00:52.667
Then you'll have to dig.

00:52.762 --> 00:54.923
It's time everyone
knew the truth.

01:20.414 --> 01:22.279
This is just wrong,

01:22.375 --> 01:24.366
digging up these graves.

01:25.127 --> 01:26.503
Why is she
making us do this?

01:26.587 --> 01:30.045
Mom has her reasons, Pete.
She'll share when she's ready.
Give her time.

01:47.692 --> 01:48.932
Look who
he's turned us into.

01:49.026 --> 01:52.518
He knows what he's done,
and he's carrying
enough guilt for all of us.

01:52.613 --> 01:54.194
But he's here,
isn't he?

01:55.032 --> 01:57.114
He needs our support.

01:57.201 --> 02:01.865
Boy, he charmed you.
Don't worry,
happens to all of us.

02:04.542 --> 02:06.203
I'm gonna go talk to her.

02:16.053 --> 02:17.634
What are we doing here,
Mom?

02:18.723 --> 02:20.884
You said we came here
to find your sister.

02:21.726 --> 02:24.217
We didn't know
you had a sister.

02:25.396 --> 02:29.230
Look, we need some answers.
Mom, what happened out here?

02:33.612 --> 02:35.227
(HONMNG)

02:47.918 --> 02:49.704
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

02:55.676 --> 02:59.043
Angela?
Angela and Alice Shaw.

03:00.556 --> 03:05.391
(CHUCKLES) Good.
That's everybody.
Welcome to Coyote Sands.

03:05.478 --> 03:10.939
My name is Dr. Chandra Suresh.
Please, follow me.
Take a snack.

03:12.777 --> 03:17.362
Playground.
The dining room.
The game room.

03:17.448 --> 03:22.067
We show movies every night.
And the best popcorn
you've ever had.

03:22.161 --> 03:25.028
You have a funny accent.
So do you.

03:26.665 --> 03:28.246
So, where are you from?

03:33.297 --> 03:36.710
These are your quarters,
and your parents
are just across the quad.

03:36.801 --> 03:38.883
Dr. Zimmerman
will show you the way.

03:41.639 --> 03:43.550
(BOTH CHATTERING)

03:43.641 --> 03:48.180
Why do they have guns?
lt's alarming, I know,
but this isn't a prison.

03:48.270 --> 03:51.888
The guards are here
for your protection.
We want to keep you safe.

03:51.982 --> 03:53.938
Come on, let's
get you settled.

04:04.829 --> 04:06.569
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

04:06.664 --> 04:08.655
| see you got
the milk and cookies.

04:10.876 --> 04:13.128
We wanted to give you
the official welcome.

04:13.212 --> 04:15.203
Welcome to Crapola Sands.

04:16.132 --> 04:17.338
l'm Charles Deveaux.

04:17.425 --> 04:20.258
The guy with
the funny accent
is Daniel Linderman,

04:20.344 --> 04:22.710
and the guy
with the glasses
is Bobby Bishop.

04:23.722 --> 04:26.464
I didn't think boys
were allowed
in the girls' bunk.

04:26.559 --> 04:28.220
Yes, yes, well,

04:28.310 --> 04:32.223
Bobby here, he wanted to
tell you how beautiful
he thought you were.

04:33.023 --> 04:34.638
I did not.
What?

04:34.733 --> 04:36.519
You don't think
she's beautiful?

04:36.610 --> 04:37.861
(EXHALES)

04:38.863 --> 04:40.694
Anyway, we just
wanted to say hi.

04:47.872 --> 04:51.114
I don't like this.
I wanna be
with Mom and Dad.

04:51.208 --> 04:53.244
We already
talked about this.

04:53.335 --> 04:56.122
It's gonna be fun.
Just like camp.

04:57.047 --> 04:58.378
Let's get you unpacked.

05:01.719 --> 05:03.300
You said pack what I need.

05:04.889 --> 05:08.723
You need clothes, Alice.
Pants, shirts, socks.

05:08.809 --> 05:11.676
And how many times
have you read
Alice in Wonderland?

05:15.274 --> 05:16.980
(SIGHS)

05:17.067 --> 05:21.857
I wanna go home,
Banana, and so do you.
Prom is coming.

05:24.033 --> 05:27.992
The doctor told Mom and Dad
that this place is gonna
make my nightmares go away.

05:28.078 --> 05:29.488
No more screaming?

05:32.041 --> 05:34.157
But what I have
is genetic,

05:34.251 --> 05:37.618
so we all need
to deal with it,
the entire family.

05:39.089 --> 05:41.922
Who snuck you out
to see Sleeping Beauty?

05:42.009 --> 05:45.877
And who gave Jackie Jacobs
an Indian burn when
she stole your barrette?

05:49.475 --> 05:52.888
I'll always be there
for you, I promise.

05:53.771 --> 05:55.932
But I need you
to be there for me, too.

05:59.735 --> 06:01.191
(EXCLAIMS)

06:01.946 --> 06:04.938
See? Everything's
gonna be fine.

06:15.125 --> 06:16.285
PETER: Mom?

06:16.377 --> 06:20.290
My sister, my parents,
they all died here.

06:20.798 --> 06:24.461
And ifwe don't come
together, ifwe don't
settle our differences,

06:25.761 --> 06:28.628
I'm afraid
history is going
to repeat itself.

06:53.914 --> 06:58.658
1961 was a different time.
Kennedy was president.

06:58.752 --> 07:00.413
We were all patriots.

07:01.505 --> 07:05.043
When the government
found out about us, they
told us they could cure us,

07:05.134 --> 07:06.965
and we believed them.

07:08.012 --> 07:11.004
And they rounded us all up,
and they put us here.

07:11.807 --> 07:13.343
What happened here?

07:13.434 --> 07:19.680
I don't know. I was lucky,
I survived, but Alice,
my entire family, didn't.

07:19.773 --> 07:23.732
So, why are we here, Mom?
You could have told us
this in a restaurant.

07:23.819 --> 07:26.060
Why here?
Why are we digging
up those bodies?

07:27.281 --> 07:29.613
I've been dreaming
about my sister.

07:32.036 --> 07:33.151
Alive.

07:34.038 --> 07:36.780
That doesn't make sense,
but my dreams often don't.

07:36.874 --> 07:39.160
They're open
to interpretation.

07:39.251 --> 07:41.993
They're confusing,
but I think, I think

07:43.464 --> 07:45.125
l have to see her
for myself.

07:45.215 --> 07:47.467
l have to find her body,
find a piece of clothing.

07:47.551 --> 07:50.258
Something, anything,
to give her
a proper burial.

07:50.346 --> 07:52.632
You should have told us
about this place,

07:53.098 --> 07:54.804
that you had a sister.

07:54.892 --> 07:57.349
I didn't want you
to know the pain. Mothers
are allowed to do that.

07:57.436 --> 07:58.972
I'm allowed
to protect you.

07:59.063 --> 08:01.349
You're absolutely
allowed to do that, Ma.

08:02.274 --> 08:03.810
It's my nightmare, Peter.

08:04.777 --> 08:08.315
I never wanted you
to know what I suffered.
I tried to forget.

08:09.073 --> 08:10.734
We made everyone forget.

08:12.117 --> 08:13.402
Who's "we"?

08:14.244 --> 08:16.326
How do you think
the Company was formed?

08:16.413 --> 08:20.656
It started here,
with a vow to never
let this happen again.

08:20.751 --> 08:25.871
We destroyed files,
erased memories.
We blackmailed, we killed,

08:26.840 --> 08:32.176
anything to keep
our existence secret.
And it worked for 50 years.

08:33.180 --> 08:35.887
Now, Noah and l have
tried to fix this
current situation,

08:35.974 --> 08:39.137
but Mr. Danko has
proved resourceful.

08:40.479 --> 08:42.515
So, that's what
you were trying to do?

08:43.315 --> 08:44.521
Yes.

08:45.734 --> 08:47.065
But you blew it?

08:47.861 --> 08:48.976
Yeah.

08:49.697 --> 08:53.281
The important thing is
to put our secret back,

08:53.367 --> 08:56.655
so we can all stop running,
return to our lives.

08:57.538 --> 08:59.745
It's time to go back
to the old methods.

09:00.457 --> 09:02.948
You mean erasing people's
memories and killing?

09:03.043 --> 09:04.453
It's a necessary evil.

09:04.545 --> 09:07.503
I'm sorry about
what happened here, Mom,

09:08.424 --> 09:11.131
but it didn't give you
the right to do the things
that you've done,

09:11.218 --> 09:12.924
and it still doesn't.

09:13.846 --> 09:15.336
We need you, Peter.

09:17.015 --> 09:18.971
I need you.
The Company tore
this family apart.

09:19.059 --> 09:20.970
I'm not gonna be
a part of it again.

09:22.938 --> 09:25.520
Peter.
I'll get him.

09:26.692 --> 09:28.057
(WHOOSHING)

09:30.946 --> 09:32.277
(GASPING)

09:39.872 --> 09:41.703
CHARLES:
You had a nightmare.

09:42.040 --> 09:45.123
(SIGHS) What's it to you?
Look, I heard you
talking to your sister,

09:45.210 --> 09:47.075
about how your nightmares
come true.

09:48.130 --> 09:50.041
Look, you're not
the only one
who's realized

09:50.132 --> 09:52.293
there's something strange
happening to them.

09:53.010 --> 09:55.501
I don't know what
you're talking about.
Linderman.

09:55.596 --> 09:59.009
How'd a pretty skirt
like you get
a scar like that?

10:00.350 --> 10:01.965
A bicycle accident.

10:11.320 --> 10:15.279
This place is one
big science experiment,
and we're the rats.

10:15.407 --> 10:21.448
You're wrong.
They're going to help us.
She's right. We're freaks.

10:22.164 --> 10:25.156
They're gonna
make us normal.
And you're blind.

10:25.250 --> 10:27.627
Why do you think
they have armed guards?

10:27.711 --> 10:31.249
We've done nothing wrong.
It's not like
we're communists.

10:31.340 --> 10:32.750
My dad said
we can trust them.

10:32.841 --> 10:36.425
This has happened before.
Nazis with the Jews.

10:36.512 --> 10:38.844
America did it,
too, with the Japs.

10:38.931 --> 10:41.638
This is different.
We're different.

10:43.393 --> 10:44.929
What was your nightmare?

10:46.897 --> 10:48.637
My dreams are confusing.

10:49.900 --> 10:51.481
They're not always right.

10:52.736 --> 10:57.571
You have to stop
being afraid
and start believing.

11:03.497 --> 11:04.862
That doctor.

11:06.625 --> 11:07.865
Suresh.

11:12.381 --> 11:13.791
Don't trust him.

11:13.882 --> 11:15.964
(DOOR OPENING)

11:16.051 --> 11:18.087
What are you talking about?

11:18.178 --> 11:21.045
Nothing. We're all
going back to sleep.

11:31.441 --> 11:33.147
My feet are cold,
Banana.

11:33.235 --> 11:35.726
That's what you get
for not bringing any socks.

11:35.821 --> 11:37.277
I'll find you some.

11:40.158 --> 11:41.819
(WHISPERING)
Say good night, Alice.

11:41.910 --> 11:43.491
(WHISPERING)
Good night, Alice.

11:49.877 --> 11:54.120
I heard what you
were saying to the boys,
about Dr. Suresh.

11:54.214 --> 11:57.502
Those boys just have
an overactive imagination.

12:02.556 --> 12:08.017
Remember when I got
an F in History? Dad took
away the TV and dessert.

12:09.187 --> 12:11.769
l was so mad that l...

12:15.861 --> 12:18.523
That night,
a hail storm
smashed his car.

12:21.909 --> 12:23.115
So?

12:31.293 --> 12:33.454
I think I can
control the weather.

12:50.771 --> 12:53.103
ls Dr. Suresh
gonna come for me?

13:02.115 --> 13:04.902
CLAIRE: Why didn't you
tell Nathan and Peter
about your sister?

13:05.786 --> 13:07.276
Where's your father?

13:09.790 --> 13:12.907
| asked for some
alone time. With you.

13:14.962 --> 13:16.418
I want to help you.

13:18.465 --> 13:22.708
l was almost your age
when I came here. lwas 16.

13:22.803 --> 13:26.045
Every other thought
was about boys
and the prom.

13:26.139 --> 13:28.130
l was so naive.

13:28.225 --> 13:33.720
lwish I had had half of
your strength. You have
courage and self-confidence.

13:34.356 --> 13:37.268
You've overcome
all those
nagging self-doubts.

13:37.943 --> 13:39.353
Maybe sometimes.

13:40.112 --> 13:41.477
Not always.

13:42.656 --> 13:45.022
(EXHALING) I'm still
figuring it out.

13:45.117 --> 13:48.655
You dug up those graves
without batting an eye.

13:48.745 --> 13:52.738
If I had had your spirit,
if I had trusted myself,

13:52.833 --> 13:55.370
maybe things would've
been different here.

13:56.003 --> 13:57.743
Doesn't answer
my question.

13:59.381 --> 14:03.090
You ever do something
so awful, something
you are so ashamed of,

14:03.176 --> 14:07.590
that you think
if you ever talk about it,
you might never stop crying?

14:09.099 --> 14:10.760
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

14:14.396 --> 14:15.977
(WIND HOWLING)

14:16.898 --> 14:20.937
Where did this come from?
This is what happened
in my dream.

14:21.028 --> 14:25.863
It's impossible. But it is.
It's her. It's Alice.

14:29.619 --> 14:30.950
Dad!

14:34.791 --> 14:36.042
Alice!

14:38.378 --> 14:40.209
Alice!

14:40.297 --> 14:42.788
Come on, we got
to get back inside.

15:13.622 --> 15:17.206
Pete, we need
to get through whatever
it is that's between us,

15:17.292 --> 15:19.908
and you're not helping
by running away every time
things get a bit tough.

15:20.003 --> 15:21.789
Running away?
So, when you just
up and disappear,

15:21.880 --> 15:25.168
you go wherever it is
that you went, instead
of staying in Washington

15:25.258 --> 15:28.295
and dealing
with the problem
that you created...

15:28.762 --> 15:30.298
(LAUGHS)

15:31.556 --> 15:35.014
Pete, you know, nobody
can look down their nose
at me better than you.

15:35.977 --> 15:39.265
1986 Mets.
You remember that?
Yeah.

15:39.356 --> 15:41.347
How Dad had two tickets
to the World Series,

15:41.441 --> 15:44.524
that he had two other
tickets to the playoffs,

15:44.653 --> 15:46.939
and you convinced me
to go to the playoffs
with him.

15:47.030 --> 15:49.362
I wanted to make sure
you got to see a game, yeah.

15:51.827 --> 15:54.284
Come on, Pete.
I couldn't have known the Mets
were gonna beat the Astros.

15:54.371 --> 15:58.831
Come on. You got
to see Mookie Wilson
in that Game 6.

15:58.917 --> 16:00.782
You saw him.
I got lucky.

16:00.877 --> 16:03.038
You got to see that game.
I got lucky.

16:04.214 --> 16:06.580
You think | conned you
into seeing a playoff game?

16:06.675 --> 16:07.915
Yes, I do.

16:08.677 --> 16:12.636
Because even
in your generosity,
Nathan, you were selfish,

16:12.722 --> 16:14.508
and that is
just who you are.

16:15.350 --> 16:16.510
Pete,

16:17.227 --> 16:20.014
we have gotta find a way
to forgive each other.

16:20.105 --> 16:22.471
We have to find
the capacity
for forgiveness,

16:22.566 --> 16:24.557
because without that...
I'm trying.

16:27.362 --> 16:28.772
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEP/NG ON TV)

16:28.864 --> 16:31.571
WOMAN ON TV:
This is the Emergency
Broadcast Network.

16:31.700 --> 16:35.443
A severe storm warning
is in effect for
the Greater Valley area.

16:37.038 --> 16:38.653
(WIND HOWLING)

16:43.837 --> 16:45.168
Claire!

16:48.258 --> 16:49.623
Claire!

16:51.178 --> 16:52.543
(GROANS)

16:54.681 --> 16:55.966
(SCREAMS)

16:58.351 --> 17:00.933
How did you find me?
Are there more
agents coming?

17:01.021 --> 17:04.889
I'm not working with
them anymore. I tried to
stop them from the inside,

17:05.025 --> 17:07.357
and they found out.
You expect me
to believe that?

17:07.444 --> 17:09.651
It's the truth.
I tried and I failed.

17:09.738 --> 17:11.603
Angela Petrelli
brought us here.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.563
Why? What business
does she have here?

17:13.658 --> 17:17.367
She was taken here
as a child. This was a place
for people with abilities.

17:17.454 --> 17:20.617
Experimenting.
And eventually murder.

17:20.707 --> 17:21.947
What?

17:22.709 --> 17:25.792
They killed hundreds.
The graves are outside.

17:27.631 --> 17:29.292
What are you doing here?

17:32.260 --> 17:33.966
I found this.

17:36.473 --> 17:39.556
Fifty years ago,
my father was
a doctor here.

17:39.643 --> 17:44.808
I came to find out what
he was doing. Now I'm not
so sure I want to know.

17:52.364 --> 17:55.902
Hello, Alice. Angela,
can I talk with you?

17:55.992 --> 17:57.653
Yes, of course,
Dr. Suresh.

17:58.662 --> 18:00.152
It's okay, Alice.

18:26.940 --> 18:28.601
Three wavy lines.

18:32.070 --> 18:34.607
Who are they?
Don't worry about them.

18:34.698 --> 18:37.064
Just focus on
the cards, okay?

18:39.202 --> 18:42.069
Let's try again.
A triangle.

18:46.835 --> 18:49.668
I'm not reading your mind,
if that's what you think.

18:49.754 --> 18:52.996
I had a dream about this,
about you showing me cards.

18:53.633 --> 18:57.296
A dream?
About this exact moment?

18:58.763 --> 19:01.095
And does everything
you dream come true?

19:01.182 --> 19:03.173
They're dreams.
They're confusing.

19:03.268 --> 19:05.224
And what else
have you dreamt about?

19:08.732 --> 19:10.097
About you.

19:11.026 --> 19:13.358
(SOFTLY) You're going
to kill everybody here.

19:14.654 --> 19:17.566
My parents, my sister.

19:23.038 --> 19:24.278
I can assure you,

19:25.332 --> 19:28.745
that's not going
to happen.
You are a good man,

19:28.835 --> 19:31.451
and you've treated us
with nothing but kindness,

19:31.546 --> 19:35.334
but I'm telling you,
it's going to get
out of your control.

19:35.925 --> 19:38.507
lfyouleave,
it destroys
all our work.

19:38.595 --> 19:42.258
Don't you see the benefits
your abilities could have
for the world?

19:42.349 --> 19:44.260
I only see my nightmares.

19:45.977 --> 19:49.595
Einstein said, "The life of
the individual has meaning..."

19:49.689 --> 19:53.307
"...only insofar as
it aids in making the life
of every living thing

19:53.401 --> 19:55.232
"nobler and
more beautiful."

19:56.029 --> 19:57.189
You've read Einstein.

19:57.280 --> 19:59.771
No. ljust dreamt
that you would say that.

20:01.910 --> 20:03.241
(EXCLAIMS)

20:05.163 --> 20:08.997
You've said yourself
that dreams are confusing,

20:09.084 --> 20:10.540
open to interpretation.

20:11.711 --> 20:14.088
Everything is going
to be fine, Angela.

20:15.298 --> 20:18.040
Now, this won't
hurt a bit.

20:20.970 --> 20:24.929
I tried to warn them.
I tried to make them stop.

20:25.016 --> 20:29.259
I tried to save them,
save Alice.
And now Alice is alive.

20:29.354 --> 20:32.346
If this is your sister,
then why is she doing this?

20:32.440 --> 20:34.146
She's angry.

20:34.818 --> 20:37.434
You don't believe me.
Storms happen.

20:37.529 --> 20:40.362
It's my sister.
What if it's not?

20:40.448 --> 20:44.908
No. I need to go find her.
I need to deal
with this alone.

20:44.994 --> 20:47.485
No, it's too dangerous
out there.

20:54.712 --> 20:56.668
(WIND CALMS)

21:07.434 --> 21:09.595
You okay?
What is it?

21:10.353 --> 21:12.890
Your mom. She's gone.

21:14.107 --> 21:15.096
(SIGHS)

21:32.542 --> 21:35.909
So what? My father
was Dr. Mengele?

21:36.004 --> 21:37.869
You don't know
what happened here.

21:38.006 --> 21:40.372
It's hard to
ignore facts.
Which are what?

21:40.508 --> 21:43.716
He worked here.
Everyone died,
